\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/alert_rule.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"alertRule.Eval\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The Grafana alert evaluation scheduler detects and logs when evaluation cycles overrun their time budget through a two-part mechanism:\\n\\n(1) SCHEDULER TICK AND CYCLE OVERRUN DETECTION:\\nThe main scheduler loop is implemented in `schedule.schedulePeriodic()` (pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go, lines 246-267), which receives ticks from a ticker and processes them. Each tick invokes `schedule.processTick()` (lines 276-422) to evaluate rules scheduled for that tick.\\n\\nThe ticker that produces regular ticks is implemented in `ticker.T.run()` (pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/ticker/ticker.go, lines 51-77). The scheduler measures how far behind schedule it is using `metrics.BehindSeconds` (set at schedule.go:256), which calculates the delay between the tick time and when the scheduler actually processes it.\\n\\nAdditionally, `metrics.SchedulePeriodicDuration` (observed at schedule.go:260) tracks how long each scheduler iteration takes, allowing detection of cycles that exceed their time budget.\\n\\n(2) OVERRUN WARNING LOG:\\nWhen an alert rule evaluation takes too long, the scheduler detects this as a dropped tick. In `schedule.runJobFn()` (lines 426-442), when `alertRule.Eval()` returns a non-nil `dropped` value, indicating that a new evaluation request arrived before the previous one completed, the scheduler logs the warning: \\\"Tick dropped because alert rule evaluation is too slow\\\" (line 438).\\n\\nThe `alertRule.Eval()` method (pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/alert_rule.go, lines 200-217) implements this detection by attempting a non-blocking read of the evaluation channel before sending a new evaluation. If a message is already waiting in the channel (from a previous tick that hasn't been processed), it returns the dropped message, signaling an evaluation cycle overrun.\\n\\nAdditional metrics track evaluation performance: `metrics.EvaluationMissed` (defined in pkg/services/ngalert/metrics/scheduler.go, line 178) counts total missed evaluations per organization and rule name, providing visibility into frequency of overruns.\"\n}\n",
